abstract: Maldives Parliament votes to impeach Vice Pres Mohamed Jameel, accusing him of dereliction of duties; Jameel, who is now in Great Britain and was elected with Pres Abdulla Yameen in 2013, says government stopped him from working; some assert impeachment is concession for imprisonment of former Pres Mohamed Nasheed, detainment seen by America and other nations as politically motivated.
lead_paragraph: Parliament in the Maldives voted overwhelmingly Tuesday to impeach Vice President Mohamed Jameel after accusing him of dereliction of duties.

headline.main: Maldives: Vice President Is Impeached in Absentia
headline.print_headline: Asia; Maldives: Vice President Is Impeached in Absentia
